"1408":"1408","1418":"1418","12 March 1397":"12 March 1397","1428":"1428","Thornton, Northumberland, England":"Thornton, Northumberland, England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","Etal Castle, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Etal, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Heron","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Herron  .","French (<b>Héron</b>): nickname for a tall, thin person, thought to resemble a heron (Old French <i>hairon</i>)."],"variants":[{"name":"Herron","meanings":["English: habitational name from Harome (North Yorkshire), from Old English <i>(æt thǣm) hārum</i> ‘at the (gray) stones’, dative plural of <i>hār</i> ‘gray, stone’.","English and Scottish: nickname probably for a tall, thin man with long legs, from Old French <i>hairon</i> ‘heron’, Anglo-Norman French <i>heron</i>, Middle English <i>heiroun</i>, <i>heyron</i>, <i>herne</i>, <i>heron</i>. Compare   Hearn   and   Heron  .","English (of Norman origin): habitational name from (Le) Héron in France (Seine-Maritime)."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Heron IV of Thornton, Esq. was born on 12 March 1397, in Northumberland, England, his father, John Heron II of Thornton, was 28 and his mother, Katherine Heron, was 23. He married Isabel Umfreville before 1418. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 15 January 1428, in Etal, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 30."},"et":{"12 March 1397–15 January 1428":"12. märts 1397–15. jaanuar 1428","1397–1428":"1397–1428","1400–1428":"1400–1428","1418–1461":"1418–1461","1370–1408":"1370–1408","1375–1428":"1375–1428","1461":"1461","1370":"1370","before 1418":"enne 1418","about 1418":"umbes 1418","1400":"1400","15 January 1428":"15. jaanuar 1428","1375":"1375","1397":"1397","5 October 1408":"5. oktoober 1408","1408":"1408","1418":"1418","12 March 1397":"12. märts 1397","1428":"1428","Thornton, Northumberland, England":"Thornton, Northumberland, England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","Etal Castle, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Etal, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"12 March 1397–15 January 1428":"12. maaliskuuta 1397–15. tammikuuta 1428","1397–1428":"1397–1428","1400–1428":"1400–1428","1418–1461":"1418–1461","1370–1408":"1370–1408","1375–1428":"1375–1428","1461":"1461","1370":"1370","before 1418":"ennen vuotta 1418","about 1418":"noin 1418","1400":"1400","15 January 1428":"15. tammikuuta 1428","1375":"1375","1397":"1397","5 October 1408":"5. lokakuuta 1408","1408":"1408","1418":"1418","12 March 1397":"12. maaliskuuta 1397","1428":"1428","Thornton, Northumberland, England":"Thornton, Northumberland, England","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","Etal Castle, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Etal, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"12 March 1397–15 January 1428":"12 mars 1397–15 janvier 1428","1397–1428":"1397–1428","1400–1428":"1400–1428","1418–1461":"1418–1461","1370–1408":"1370–1408","1375–1428":"1375–1428","1461":"1461","1370":"1370","before 1418":"avant 1418","about 1418":"environ 141